        <title>Communication, Dissemination and Outreach Plan</title>
        <description>I will take the opportunity to inform about the key role of the Ocean in climate and to communicate about the major findings of this project to the general public through press releases, social media and different outreach events. I will participate to ‘La Fête de la Science’ with a scientifically-inclined general audience or ‘Les Etoiles brillent pour tous’ that raise awareness of climate change issues to isolated citizens in hospitals, jails, senior citizen’s homes and remote countryside. Participating in such events will maximize public exposure of my research, and allow direct engagement with the public. I will also continue to communicate my findings to the outreach section of the GEOTRACES website and to regional schools.Moreover, I will share the results of this project with the international scientific community during the major conferences for marine geochemistry such as the Goldschmidt and Ocean Science Meeting conferences. The findings of this project will also be published in peer-reviewed scientific publications.</description>
